  {
    "id": "_948973_1",
    "title": "Welcome ",
    "body": "<p><strong>Welcome to Copyright Law (LAWS5206)</strong></p><br><p>Hi everyone</p><br><p>Welcome to&nbsp;<strong>LAWS5206 Copyright Law. </strong>I will be your course coordinator for this course. I will be joined by&nbsp;<strong>Professor John Swinson</strong>, who will co-deliver the course with me over two very full weekends on 28 Feb/1 March and 11/12 April. </p><br><p>All course-learning resources are located on Blackboard site which should now be available. It is very important that you regularly check the Blackboard site for any new resources and important announcements.&nbsp; </p><br><p>As you probably know, all UQ courses have now been upgraded to Ultra.&nbsp;&nbsp;Explore the Student Tour to familiarise yourself with the updated features and layout \u2013&nbsp;<a href=\"https://echo360.net.au/media/1def1638-62ca-4431-b28c-06d1028aa738/public\"><span style=\"color: #96607d\">Click here for the student tour video.</span></a></p><br><p>The Course Profile can be accessed via the link at the top of the content page on your course Blackboard site. Please ensure you have thoroughly read this document, as it contains details of the course objectives and structure, assessment information, and UQ policies regarding assessment.</p><br><p>We look forward to seeing you on 28 Feb.</p><br><p>Kind regards,&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Ben Gardiner</strong></p><br>",
